                <h2>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Booster Bonus Phase</h2>

                <p>In this  variation of the Bonus phase the Participants will get certain points for the  correct answer (X Points, which may be equal to 100, 200, 300 or so on). This  Bonus Phase shall be offered for a specific time periods on the days decided by  Warid. The incorrect answer shall give 50 Points. Before the start of the Bonus  Phase, the Participant shall be informed about the value of X.</p>
                <h2><small>Example:</small></h2>
                <p>Value of X = 200.&nbsp; Value of ‘X’ is for illustration purposes  only, it may change.&nbsp; Wrong answer will  give you 50 points. </p>
                <ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>1st  Question = 200</li>
                        <li>2nd  Question = 200</li>
                        <li>3rd  Question = 50 (Wrong Answer)</li>
                        <li>4th  Question = 200</li>
                        <li>5th  Question = 50 (Wrong Answer)</li>
                        <li>6th  Question = 200</li>
                    </ul>
                </ul>

                <h2>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Double Bonus Phase</h2>

                <p>In this variation of the  Bonus Phase, the Participant will be gaining more points for each question he  answers for a set of questions.&nbsp; For  example, for the coming 7 questions, you will get double the points from the  last correct answer. The incorrect answer shall not affect the points earning  for the next correct answer, however, the incorrect answer shall give 50 Points  to the Participant. Before the start of the Bonus Phase, the Participant shall  be informed about the value of X.&nbsp; </p>
                <h2><small>Example:</small></h2>
                <p>Value of X = 1000.&nbsp; Value of ‘X’ is for illustration purposes  only, it may change.&nbsp; Wrong answer will  give you 50 points.</p>
                <ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>1st  Question = 1000</li>
                        <li>2nd  Question = 2000</li>
                        <li>3rd  Question = 50 (Wrong Answered)</li>
                        <li>4th  Question = 4000</li>
                        <li>5th  Question = 50 (Wrong Answered)</li>
                        <li>6th  Question = 8000</li>
                    </ul>
                </ul>
                <h2>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ladder Bonus Phase </h2>
                <p>In this  variation of Bonus Phase, the first correct answer shall give different Points  for the correct answer which shall be informed to the Participant before the  start of the phase. For the subsequent correct answers the Participant will be  gaining more points (X Points which may be 50, 100, 200 or so on) in addition  to the Points earned for the last correct answer. This Bonus Phase shall have a  certain number of questions in it. &nbsp;For  example X=50, then for the coming 7, 15, 20 or more questions as may be this  Bonus Phase shall contain, the Participant will get 50 more points for the  correct answer as compared to the points earned for the last correct answer.&nbsp; Wrong answer will give 50 points to the  Participant. Before the start of the Bonus Phase, the Participant shall be  informed about the Points of the first correct answer, value of X and the  number of questions in the Bonus Phase.&nbsp; </p>
                <h2><small>Example:</small></h2>
                <p>The First correct answer will give 150  Points, and the Value of X = 50.&nbsp; Value  of ‘X’ is for illustration purposes only, it may change.&nbsp; </p>
                <ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>1st  Question = 150</li>
                        <li>2nd  Question = 200</li>
                        <li>3rd  Question = 50 (Wrong Answered)</li>
                        <li>4th  Question = 250</li>
                        <li>5th  Question = 300</li>
                        <li>6th  Question = 50 (Wrong Answered)</li>
                        <li>7th  Question = 350</li>
                    </ul>
                </ul>

                <h2>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Magic Question  Phase: </h2>
                <p>In this Bonus Phase  variation, a set of Questions shall be sent to the Participant which may be 5,  10, 20 or 30 questions and he shall reply to such Questions within a specific  time which may be 1, 2, or 3 hours. During the Bonus Phase one random Question shall  be received by the Participant which shall be a magic Question and it shall  give different value of Points (X value of Points which may be 1000, 2000, 5000  and so on). Before the start of the Bonus Phase, the Participant shall be  informed for the number of Questions in the set, the time of the Bonus Phase  and the value of X Points.</p>
                <h2><small>Example:</small></h2>
                <p>Value of X = 5000.&nbsp; Value of ‘X’ is for illustration purposes  only, it may change.&nbsp; Wrong answer will  give you 50 points.</p>
                <ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>1st  Question = 100</li>
                        <li>2nd  Question = 100</li>
                        <li>3rd  Question = 50 (Wrong Answered)</li>
                        <li>4th  Question = 100</li>
                        <li>5th  Question = 5000</li>
                    </ul>
                </ul>

                <h2>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In a Row /  Package Bonus Phase: </h2>
                <p>In this  variation of the Bonus Phase, the Participant shall get different Points for  correctly answering the last Question of the Phase which may be 2000, 3000,  5000 or 10000 (X Points). The correct answer to the remaining Questions shall  give 100 Points as given in the Basic Mode. The incorrect answer will give 50  Points. There shall be a set of Questions in this Phase that may be 10, 15, 20  or more questions. &nbsp;</p>
